<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 16 at 2:12PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Comanche, northwestern Cotton and southeastern Tillman Counties
through 245 PM CDT...
At 212 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hollister, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Faxon, Hollister and Loveland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
